The paper deals with the problem of recovering an image that has been altered by an unknown black box operator, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the conditions under which the problem is solvable, which is related to information theory (cs.IT), and provides a simple algorithm for solving the problem, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
